Problem-Write a program to input a string and also count vowels in the given string.

Code:
     package d2009;
 
public class vowels {
    public static void main(String[] args)
    
    {
        String str = "My name is AK";
        str = str.toLowerCase();
        int count = 0;
 
        for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            if (str.charAt(i) == 'a' || str.charAt(i) == 'e'
                || str.charAt(i) == 'i'
                || str.charAt(i) == 'o'
                || str.charAt(i) == 'u') {
                count++;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(
            "Total no of vowels in string are: " + count);
    }
}

Input-'My name is AK'
Output- Vowels=4

Input-'My name is 'ASHWINI KUMAR'
Output- Vowels=8

Explanation-In the above program we are inputting a string and
            counting the number of vowels in the string.
            
